{"orig":"/Users/kalaverin/src/lang/nim/lib/pure/parsecsv.nim","nimble":"stdlib","moduleDescription":"This module implements a simple high performance <span id=\"csv_1\">CSV</span> (<span id=\"comma-separated-value_1\">comma separated value</span>) parser.\n<h1><a class=\"toc-backref\" id=\"basic-usage\" href=\"#basic-usage\">Basic usage</a></h1><p><pre class=\"listing\"><span class=\"Keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">std</span><span class=\"Operator\">/</span><span class=\"Identifier\">parsecsv</span>\n<span class=\"Keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">std</span><span class=\"Operator\">/</span><span class=\"Identifier\">os</span> <span class=\"Keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">paramStr</span>\n<span class=\"Keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">std</span><span class=\"Operator\">/</span><span class=\"Identifier\">streams</span> <span class=\"Keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">newFileStream</span>\n\n<span class=\"Keyword\">var</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">s</span> <span class=\"Operator\">=</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">newFileStream</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"Identifier\">paramStr</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"DecNumber\">1</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">fmRead</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"Keyword\">if</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">s</span> <span class=\"Operator\">==</span> <span class=\"Keyword\">nil</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">:</span>\n  <span class=\"Identifier\">quit</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"StringLit\">&quot;cannot open the file&quot;</span> <span class=\"Operator\">&amp;</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">paramStr</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"DecNumber\">1</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"Keyword\">var</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">x</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">CsvParser</span>\n<span class=\"Identifier\">open</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"Identifier\">x</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">s</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">paramStr</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"DecNumber\">1</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"Keyword\">while</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">readRow</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"Identifier\">x</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">:</span>\n  <span class=\"Identifier\">echo</span> <span class=\"StringLit\">&quot;new row: &quot;</span>\n  <span class=\"Keyword\">for</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">val</span> <span class=\"Keyword\">in</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">items</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"Identifier\">x</span><span class=\"Operator\">.</span><span class=\"Identifier\">row</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">:</span>\n    <span class=\"Identifier\">echo</span> <span class=\"StringLit\">&quot;##&quot;</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">val</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"StringLit\">&quot;##&quot;</span>\n<span class=\"Identifier\">close</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"Identifier\">x</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span></pre></p>\n<p>For CSV files with a header row, the header can be read and then used as a reference for item access with <a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#rowEntry,CsvParser,string\">rowEntry</a>:</p>\n<p><pre class=\"listing\"><span class=\"Keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">std</span><span class=\"Operator\">/</span><span class=\"Identifier\">parsecsv</span>\n\n<span class=\"Comment\"># Prepare a file</span>\n<span class=\"Keyword\">let</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">content</span> <span class=\"Operator\">=</span> <span class=\"LongStringLit\">&quot;&quot;&quot;One,Two,Three,Four\n1,2,3,4\n10,20,30,40\n100,200,300,400\n&quot;&quot;&quot;</span>\n<span class=\"Identifier\">writeFile</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"StringLit\">&quot;temp.csv&quot;</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">content</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"Keyword\">var</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">p</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">CsvParser</span>\n<span class=\"Identifier\">p</span><span class=\"Operator\">.</span><span class=\"Identifier\">open</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"StringLit\">&quot;temp.csv&quot;</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"Identifier\">p</span><span class=\"Operator\">.</span><span class=\"Identifier\">readHeaderRow</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"Keyword\">while</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">p</span><span class=\"Operator\">.</span><span class=\"Identifier\">readRow</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">:</span>\n  <span class=\"Identifier\">echo</span> <span class=\"StringLit\">&quot;new row: &quot;</span>\n  <span class=\"Keyword\">for</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">col</span> <span class=\"Keyword\">in</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">items</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"Identifier\">p</span><span class=\"Operator\">.</span><span class=\"Identifier\">headers</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">:</span>\n    <span class=\"Identifier\">echo</span> <span class=\"StringLit\">&quot;##&quot;</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">col</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"StringLit\">&quot;:&quot;</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"Identifier\">p</span><span class=\"Operator\">.</span><span class=\"Identifier\">rowEntry</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"Identifier\">col</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"StringLit\">&quot;##&quot;</span>\n<span class=\"Identifier\">p</span><span class=\"Operator\">.</span><span class=\"Identifier\">close</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"Punctuation\">)</span></pre></p>\n\n<h1><a class=\"toc-backref\" id=\"see-also\" href=\"#see-also\">See also</a></h1><ul class=\"simple\"><li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"streams.html\">streams module</a> for using <a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#open,CsvParser,Stream,string,char,char,char\">open proc</a> and other stream processing (like <a class=\"reference external\" href=\"streams.html#close,Stream\">close proc</a>)</li>\n<li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"parseopt.html\">parseopt module</a> for a command line parser</li>\n<li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"parsecfg.html\">parsecfg module</a> for a configuration file parser</li>\n<li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"parsexml.html\">parsexml module</a> for a XML / HTML parser</li>\n<li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"parsesql.html\">parsesql module</a> for a SQL parser</li>\n<li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"lib.html#pure-libraries-parsers\">other parsers</a> for other parsers</li>\n</ul>\n","entries":[{"name":"CsvRow","type":"skType","line":76,"col":10,"code":"CsvRow = seq[string]","description":"A row in a CSV file."},{"name":"CsvParser","type":"skType","line":77,"col":13,"code":"CsvParser = object of BaseLexer\n  row*: CsvRow\n  headers*: seq[string]","description":"<p>The parser object.</p>\n<p>It consists of two public fields:</p>\n<ul class=\"simple\"><li><tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">row</span></span></tt> is the current row</li>\n<li><tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">headers</span></span></tt> are the columns that are defined in the csv file (read using <a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#readHeaderRow,CsvParser\">readHeaderRow</a>). Used with <a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#rowEntry,CsvParser,string\">rowEntry</a>).</li>\n</ul>\n"},{"name":"CsvError","type":"skType","line":91,"col":12,"code":"CsvError = object of IOError","description":"An exception that is raised if a parsing error occurs."},{"name":"open","type":"skProc","line":107,"col":0,"code":"proc open(self: var CsvParser; input: Stream; filename: string; separator = ',';\n          quote = '\\\"'; escape = '\\x00'; skipInitialSpace = false) {.\n    raises: [IOError, OSError], tags: [ReadIOEffect], forbids: [].}","signature":{"arguments":[{"name":"self","type":"var CsvParser"},{"name":"input","type":"Stream"},{"name":"filename","type":"string"},{"name":"separator","type":"","default":"','"},{"name":"quote","type":"","default":"'\\\"'"},{"name":"escape","type":"","default":"'\\x00'"},{"name":"skipInitialSpace","type":"","default":"false"}],"pragmas":["raises: [IOError, OSError]","tags: [ReadIOEffect]","forbids: []"]},"description":"Initializes the parser with an input stream. <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">Filename</span></span></tt> is only used for nice error messages. The parser's behaviour can be controlled by the diverse optional parameters:<ul class=\"simple\"><li><tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">separator</span></span></tt>: character used to separate fields</li>\n<li><tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">quote</span></span></tt>: Used to quote fields containing special characters like <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">separator</span></span></tt>, <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">quote</span></span></tt> or new-line characters. '\\0' disables the parsing of quotes.</li>\n<li><tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">escape</span></span></tt>: removes any special meaning from the following character; '\\0' disables escaping; if escaping is disabled and <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">quote</span></span></tt> is not '\\0', two <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">quote</span></span></tt> characters are parsed one literal <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">quote</span></span></tt> character.</li>\n<li><tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">skipInitialSpace</span></span></tt>: If true, whitespace immediately following the <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">separator</span></span></tt> is ignored.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>See also:</p>\n<ul class=\"simple\"><li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#open,CsvParser,string,char,char,char\">open proc</a> which creates the file stream for you</li>\n</ul>\n"},{"name":"open","type":"skProc","line":141,"col":0,"code":"proc open(self: var CsvParser; filename: string; separator = ','; quote = '\\\"';\n          escape = '\\x00'; skipInitialSpace = false) {.\n    raises: [CsvError, IOError, OSError], tags: [ReadIOEffect], forbids: [].}","signature":{"arguments":[{"name":"self","type":"var CsvParser"},{"name":"filename","type":"string"},{"name":"separator","type":"","default":"','"},{"name":"quote","type":"","default":"'\\\"'"},{"name":"escape","type":"","default":"'\\x00'"},{"name":"skipInitialSpace","type":"","default":"false"}],"pragmas":["raises: [CsvError, IOError, OSError]","tags: [ReadIOEffect]","forbids: []"]},"description":"Similar to the <a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#open,CsvParser,Stream,string,char,char,char\">other open proc</a>, but creates the file stream for you."},{"name":"processedRows","type":"skProc","line":202,"col":0,"code":"proc processedRows(self: var CsvParser): int {.inline, raises: [], tags: [],\n    forbids: [].}","signature":{"return":"int","arguments":[{"name":"self","type":"var CsvParser"}],"pragmas":["inline","raises: []","tags: []","forbids: []"]},"description":"<p>Returns number of the processed rows.</p>\n<p>But even if <a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#readRow,CsvParser,int\">readRow</a> arrived at EOF then processed rows counter is incremented.</p>\n"},{"name":"readRow","type":"skProc","line":227,"col":0,"code":"proc readRow(self: var CsvParser; columns = 0): bool {.\n    raises: [IOError, OSError, CsvError], tags: [ReadIOEffect], forbids: [].}","signature":{"return":"bool","arguments":[{"name":"self","type":"var CsvParser"},{"name":"columns","type":"","default":"0"}],"pragmas":["raises: [IOError, OSError, CsvError]","tags: [ReadIOEffect]","forbids: []"]},"description":"<p>Reads the next row; if <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">columns</span></span></tt> &gt; 0, it expects the row to have exactly this many columns. Returns false if the end of the file has been encountered else true.</p>\n<p>Blank lines are skipped.</p>\n"},{"name":"close","type":"skProc","line":292,"col":0,"code":"proc close(self: var CsvParser) {.inline, raises: [IOError, OSError],\n                                  tags: [WriteIOEffect], forbids: [].}","signature":{"arguments":[{"name":"self","type":"var CsvParser"}],"pragmas":["inline","raises: [IOError, OSError]","tags: [WriteIOEffect]","forbids: []"]},"description":"Closes the parser <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">self</span></span></tt> and its associated input stream."},{"name":"readHeaderRow","type":"skProc","line":296,"col":0,"code":"proc readHeaderRow(self: var CsvParser) {.raises: [IOError, OSError, CsvError],\n    tags: [ReadIOEffect], forbids: [].}","signature":{"arguments":[{"name":"self","type":"var CsvParser"}],"pragmas":["raises: [IOError, OSError, CsvError]","tags: [ReadIOEffect]","forbids: []"]},"description":"Reads the first row and creates a look-up table for column numbers See also:<ul class=\"simple\"><li><a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#rowEntry,CsvParser,string\">rowEntry proc</a></li>\n</ul>\n"},{"name":"rowEntry","type":"skProc","line":322,"col":0,"code":"proc rowEntry(self: var CsvParser; entry: string): var string {.\n    raises: [KeyError], tags: [], forbids: [].}","signature":{"return":"var string","arguments":[{"name":"self","type":"var CsvParser"},{"name":"entry","type":"string"}],"pragmas":["raises: [KeyError]","tags: []","forbids: []"]},"description":"<p>Accesses a specified <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">entry</span></span></tt> from the current row.</p>\n<p>Assumes that <a class=\"reference external\" href=\"#readHeaderRow,CsvParser\">readHeaderRow</a> has already been called.</p>\n<p>If specified <tt class=\"docutils literal\"><span class=\"pre\"><span class=\"Identifier\">entry</span></span></tt> does not exist, raises KeyError.</p>\n"}]}